    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document describes a mechanism for encrypting traffic encapsulated using the Locator/ID Separation Protocol (LISP).  The design describes how key exchange is achieved using existing LISP control-plane mechanisms as well as how to secure the LISP data plane from third-party surveillance attacks.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
